---Description
The table contains data about various transportation routes, including details such as origin 
and destination cities and states, distances, and associated rates. It can be used for 
route optimization, cost analysis, and transit time estimation.

COLUMN                          |              TYPE         |         COMMENTS   
ROUTE_ID                        |             STRING        |A unique identifier for each transportation route in the dataset, allowing for easy reference and management of routes.
ORIGIN_CITY                     |             STRING        |The city from which the transportation route begins, providing context for the starting point of the journey.
ORIGIN_STATE                    |             STRING        |The state associated with the origin city, indicating the broader geographical area from which the route starts.
DESTINATION_CITY                |             STRING        |The city at the end of the transportation route, representing the intended endpoint of the journey.
DESTINATION_STATE               |             STRING        |The state associated with the destination city, helping to identify the geographical location where the route concludes.
TYPICALY_DISTANCE_MILES         |             BIGINT        |The average distance of the route measured in miles, useful for calculating travel time and costs.
BASE_RATE_PER_MILES             |             DOUBLE        |The standard rate charged for each mile traveled on the route, essential for pricing and cost analysis.
FUEL_SURCHARGE_RATE             |             DOUBLE        |The additional charge applied to the base rate that accounts for fluctuating fuel prices, impacting overall transportation costs.
TYPICAL_TRANSIT_DAYS            |             BIGINT        |The average number of days required to complete the journey along the route, providing insight into expected delivery times.

--SAMPLE DATA
What are the top 5 longest routes by distance?
--SQL:
     SELECT `route_id`, `origin_city`, `origin_state`, `destination_city`, `destination_state`, `typical_distance_miles`
FROM `datawerhouse1`.`bronze`.`routes`
ORDER BY `typical_distance_miles` DESC
LIMIT 5;
